wikipedia_page.main: Frederick Alexander Macquisten KC (23 July 1870 in Inverkip, Scotland – 29 February 1940 in Walton-on-Thames, England) was a British lawyer and politician. He was the son of Reverend Dr. Alexander Macquisten, the minister of Inverkip Parish Church.

response: *Frederick Alexander Macquisten; MP for Glasgow Springburn (1918–1922) and Argyllshire (1924–1940)
